Algebraically, if $f(x) = x^4$ and $g(x) = 2x + 3$ then

$(f \circ g)(x) = f(g(x))$
$= f(2x + 3)$ {$g$ operates on $x$ first}
$= (2x + 3)^4$ {$f$ operates on $g(x)$ next}

and $(g \circ f)(x) = g(f(x))$
$= g(x^4)$ {$f$ operates on $x$ first}
$= 2(x^4) + 3$ {$g$ operates on $f(x)$ next}
$= 2x^4 + 3$

So, $f(g(x)) \neq g(f(x))$.

In general, $(f \circ g)(x) \neq (g \circ f)(x)$.
